# Constant Fold Arithmetic Functions

## Description

Evaluates arithmetic functions (ABS, CEIL, FLOOR, ROUND, SQRT, POWER,
etc.) at compile time when all arguments are constants. Eliminates
per-row function evaluation.

**When to apply**: Arithmetic function with all-constant arguments.

**Why it works**: Deterministic functions produce the same result for
the same inputs. If inputs are known at plan time, compute once.

## Relational Algebra

```algebra
sigma[ABS(const)](R) -> sigma[result](R)
pi[ROUND(3.14159, 2)](R) -> pi[3.14](R)
```

## Implementation

```rust
rw!("fold-abs"; "(abs ?a)" => { Fold1("?a", fn_abs) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-ceil"; "(ceil ?a)" => { Fold1("?a", fn_ceil) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-floor"; "(floor ?a)" => { Fold1("?a", fn_floor) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-round"; "(round ?a ?b)" => { Fold2("?a", "?b", fn_round) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-sqrt"; "(sqrt ?a)" => { Fold1("?a", fn_sqrt) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-power"; "(power ?a ?b)" => { Fold2("?a", "?b", fn_power) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-exp"; "(exp ?a)" => { Fold1("?a", fn_exp) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-ln"; "(ln ?a)" => { Fold1("?a", fn_ln) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-log"; "(log ?a ?b)" => { Fold2("?a", "?b", fn_log) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-mod"; "(mod ?a ?b)" => { Fold2("?a", "?b", fn_mod) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Before: SQRT(144) evaluated per row
SELECT id, SQRT(144) AS val FROM t;
-- After: constant 12.0
SELECT id, 12.0 AS val FROM t;
```

```sql
-- Negative: column reference
SELECT SQRT(area) FROM parcels;
-- Cannot fold: area is not a constant
```

